i dont think it will 💀 The Toyota Supra was first introduced in 1978 as a more powerful, larger derivative of the Toyota Celica. It has gone through five generations: A40/A50 (1978–1981), A60 (1981–1986), A70 (1986–1993), A80 (1993–2002), and A90 (2019–present). Each generation has brought significant advancements in performance and technology. The fourth-generation Supra (A80) is perhaps the most iconic, featuring the 2JZ-GTE engine. This 3.0-liter twin-turbocharged inline-six engine is renowned for its durability and immense tuning potential, easily handling power upgrades well beyond its stock 276 horsepower rating due to its robust construction. The Supra A80 became a cultural icon, largely due to its appearance in the first "Fast & Furious" movie, where it was driven by Paul Walker's character. This exposure significantly boosted the Supra's popularity and cemented its status as a legendary sports car. The Supra has a rich motorsport history, particularly in Japanese touring car championships and endurance racing. It has competed successfully in events like the Super GT series and the 24 Hours of Le Mans, showcasing its performance capabilities on the track. The A80 Supra was noted for its advanced aerodynamics and design. It featured a distinctive rear spoiler, a long hood, and a sleek, curvaceous body. Its design contributed to excellent high-speed stability and a drag coefficient of just 0.32, aiding both performance and fuel efficiency. After a 17-year hiatus, Toyota revived the Supra in 2019 with the A90 model. This fifth-generation Supra was developed in collaboration with BMW and shares its platform and engine with the BMW Z4. The A90 is powered by a 3.0-liter turbocharged inline-six engine, producing 335 to 382 horsepower, depending on the model year, and continues to carry the legacy of its predecessors with modern performance and technology. There is no such car as the Audi i8. The "i8" is actually a model produced by BMW, a different German automaker. The BMW i8 is a plug-in hybrid sports car that combines a turbocharged three-cylinder engine with an electric motor, producing 369 horsepower and 420 lb-ft of torque. It has a sleek, futuristic design and advanced technology features like a heads-up display and a digital instrument cluster. The i8 is known for its exceptional fuel efficiency, with an estimated 69 mpg-e combined, as well as its impressive acceleration, going from 0-60 mph in just 4.2 seconds. Audi, on the other hand, has its own lineup of vehicles, including the R8, which is a high-performance sports car with a V10 engine and all-wheel drive. If you're looking for a similar car from Audi, the R8 would be a more comparable option, but it's a very different vehicle from the BMW i8 in terms of design, performance, and features.
